From Fred Itua, Abuja The Senate, has just declared the embattled Comptroller General of Nigerian Customs Service (NCS), Col. Hameed Ali (retd) unfit to hold any public office. Ali has also been urged toâ€Ž resign from office, following his refusal to wear his Service uniform. The decision of the Senate, followed an 1.35 minute closed door session, where lawmakers brainstormed on the issue. The Attorney-General of the Federation (AGF) and Minister of Justice, Mr. Abubakar Malami, also came under fire, over a letter he wrote to the Senate, wherein he urged it to maintain status quo ante on the appearance of Ali. 